newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ weekly movement falls to 5.326 mln gallons.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ weekly movement falls to 5.326 mln gallons.

text.p: The Florida Citrus Processors Association said frozen concentrated orange juice movement into trade channels for the week ended May 3 was 5,326,400 gallons compared with 5,715,115 gallons last week.
Imports were 468,411 gallons compared with 298,323 gallons the previous week.
There were 7,780 domestic receipts for this week compared with 3,695 the previous week.
Retail movement was 958,851 gallons, while bulk movement was 3,870,119 gallons.
Current season cumulative movement was 117,095,319 gallons.
The final total pack for the season is 207,917,836 gallons.
